						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab built into the wall of Hanumān temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>Trailōkyamalla (Taila III)—A.D. 1154.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated in the king's <hi rend="bold">regnal year 6, [Bhāva], Pushya, śu 24, Friday, Uttarāyaṇa-saṁkrānti.</hi> The <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> occurred on A.D. 1154, December 20, Monday whereas the <hi rend="italic">saṁkrānti</hi> occurred on December 25, Saturday.</p>						

						<p>The inscription refers to the <hi rend="italic">Mahājanas</hi> of [Go]ṭṭe, a <hi rend="italic">sarvanamasya-agrahāra.</hi> The details are lost as the record is built in.</p>						

						</summary>
